      • legalCascadingPlan

        public static boolean legalCascadingPlan(long bytesToBeAvailable,
                         EvictionPlan plan,
                         BlockMetadataManagerView managerView)
                                  throws IOException
        Checks whether the plan is legal for an evictor with cascading eviction feature like LRUEvictor. The plan is legal when the requested space can be satisfied, and there is enough space in lower tier to move in blocks from upper tier.
        Parameters:
        bytesToBeAvailable - requested bytes to be available after eviction
        plan - the eviction plan
        managerView - view of the meta data manager
        Returns:
        true if the above requirements are satisfied, otherwise false.
        Throws:
        IOException
